So, even if the average consumer can afford an electric car, many live too far from a charging station or don’t have access to a place where they can charge their vehicle.

And even so, researchers are not sure if EV’s are really the end-all, be-all, especially as trends like people using diggers replace heavy equipment batteries with hydrogen fuel cells.

Powered by hydrogen made with renewable energy sources, hydrogen fuel technology is much more efficient and provides renewable energy, which is something the world desperately needs right not.

Poseidon Networks’ Renewable Minigrids Power the Future

With cutting-edge technology combined with groups of renewable, decentralized, greener generators, Poseidon Networks is bringing the future to the present, helping organizations make the shift to a more sustainable business.

“We actually see handheld generators for divers, a new announcement that we made within the last 90 days,” Doug Stott, Founder and CEO of Poseidon Networks explained. “We’re really investing in a mini grid technology that can convert diver’s bottles into a renewable generator that basically converts the CO2 regional gas into power at about nine to one efficiency.”
